ration\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those Trump-era sanctions\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3274}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3296}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fourteen members of this year's Olympic Refugee Team were from Iran.\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3388, \"end\": 3400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Refugee Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3411, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999949740375879, \"rank\": 5.013131395261272e-06, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fourteen members\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3364}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Afghanistan,sanctions are causing famine.\", \"from\": 3418, \"to\": 3462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3421, \"end\": 3432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999998657240302, \"rank\": 1.3427572289393922e-07, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 3433, \"to\": 3442}, {\"ngram\": \"famine\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, head of the International Rescue Committee and former U.K. Foreign Minister David Miliband told senators that sanctions were \\\"the proximate cause of this starvation crisis.\\\"\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3484, \"end\": 3514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Rescue_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Rescue Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Rescue_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Rescue_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3526, \"end\": 3530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999998972271, \"rank\": 1.029316914120413e-10, \"text\": \"U.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3548, \"end\": 3562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Miliband\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Miliband\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Miliband\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Miliband\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 3472, \"to\": 3476}, {\"ngram\": \"senators\", \"from\": 3568, \"to\": 3576}, {\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3591}, {\"ngram\": \"the proximate cause\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3617}, {\"ngram\": \"this starvation crisis\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3643}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Five of the Refugee Team came from Afghanistan.\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3658, \"end\": 3670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Refugee Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3681, \"end\": 3692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999998657240302, \"rank\": 1.3427572289393922e-07, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These 37 athletes brought cheering audiences to their feet, on the banks of the Seine and on screens around the world.\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3775, \"end\": 3780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999221490755, \"rank\": 7.785122692530705e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These 37 athletes\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3712}, {\"ngram\": \"cheering audiences\", \"from\": 3721, \"to\": 3739}, {\"ngram\": \"their feet\", \"from\": 3743, \"to\": 3753}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3767}, {\"ngram\": \"screens\", \"from\": 3788, \"to\": 3795}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the Taekwondo academy in a Jordanian refugee camp that produced an Olympian.\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3827, \"end\": 3836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2540015897930858e-20, \"text\": \"Taekwondo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\"}, {\"begin\": 3890, \"end\": 3898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999470492199, \"rank\": 5.290248470939318e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Jordanian refugee camp\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 3872}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yahya's journey is a powerful testament to resilience and hope.\", \"from\": 3901, \"to\": 3964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3901, \"end\": 3906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_the_Baptist\", \"score\": 0.999986112928147, \"rank\": 1.3887264305456459e-05, \"text\": \"Yahya\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_the_Baptist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_the_Baptist\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a powerful testament\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 3940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us celebrate him and the rest of the@RefugeesOlympicTeam competing at the#Paris2024Olympics!https://t.co/VAkJOHrzH5pic.twitter.com/CFsFSdpbbm - UNHCR, the UN Refugee Agency (@Refugees)August 11, 2024 But for all the triumph and beauty of the Refugee Team - and all that these young people have accomplished despite extraordinary hardship - the stark reality is that global mass displacement has become the new normal.\", \"from\": 3966, \"to\": 4391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4126, \"end\": 4143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_High_Commissioner_for_Refugees\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UN Refugee Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_High_Commissioner_for_Refugees\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_High_Commissioner_for_Refugees\"}, {\"begin\": 4216, \"end\": 4228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Refugee Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 3972}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 3999}, {\"ngram\": \"the#Paris2024Olympics!https://t.co/VAkJOHrzH5pic.twitter.com\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4100}, {\"ngram\": \"CFsFSdpbbm - UNHCR\", \"from\": 4101, \"to\": 4119}, {\"ngram\": \"@Refugees)August\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4160}, {\"ngram\": \"all the triumph\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4193}, {\"ngram\": \"beauty\", \"from\": 4198, \"to\": 4204}, {\"ngram\": \"these young people\", \"from\": 4240, \"to\": 4258}, {\"ngram\": \"extraordinary hardship\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4307}, {\"ngram\": \"the stark reality\", \"from\": 4310, \"to\": 4327}, {\"ngram\": \"global mass displacement\", \"from\": 4336, \"to\": 4360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And whatever the specific conditions that forced each of them to leave their homes, U.S. policy is one of the factors that made things worse in their countries.\", \"from\": 4392, \"to\": 4552, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the specific conditions\", \"from\": 4405, \"to\": 4428}, {\"ngram\": \"their homes\", \"from\": 4463, \"to\": 4474}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. policy\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4487}, {\"ngram\": \"the factors\", \"from\": 4498, \"to\": 4509}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 4520, \"to\": 4526}, {\"ngram\": \"their countries\", \"from\": 4536, \"to\": 4551}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Giving these world-class athletes a chance to compete in the Olympic games was a gift - to them and to us.\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4660, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these world-class athletes\", \"from\": 4561, \"to\": 4587}, {\"ngram\": \"a chance\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4596}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic games\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4628}, {\"ngram\": \"a gift\", \"from\": 4633, \"to\": 4639}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4657, \"to\": 4659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But at the end of the day, the need for such a team speaks to our failure to reverse the conditions that displace people in the first place - including by ending U.S. economic sanctions.\", \"from\": 4661, \"to\": 4847, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 4668, \"to\": 4675}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4686}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 4688, \"to\": 4696}, {\"ngram\": \"such a team\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4712}, {\"ngram\": \"our failure\", \"from\": 4723, \"to\": 4734}, {\"ngram\": \"the conditions\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4760}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4775, \"to\": 4781}, {\"ngram\": \"the first place\", \"from\": 4785, \"to\": 4800}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. economic sanctions\", \"from\": 4823, \"to\": 4846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medals are great.\", \"from\": 4849, \"to\": 4866, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Medals\", \"from\": 4849, \"to\": 4855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But would not it be better if these amazing athletes could win the right to return safely home?\", \"from\": 4867, \"to\": 4962, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these amazing athletes\", \"from\": 4897, \"to\": 4919}, {\"ngram\": \"the right\", \"from\": 4930, \"to\": 4939}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phyllis Bennis is a fellow of the Institute for Policy Studies.\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 5027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4964, \"end\": 4978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phyllis_Bennis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phyllis Bennis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phyllis_Bennis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phyllis_Bennis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fellow\", \"from\": 4982, \"to\": 4990}, {\"ngram\": \"the Institute\", \"from\": 4994, \"to\": 5007}, {\"ngram\": \"Policy Studies\", \"from\": 5012, \"to\": 5026}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This op-ed was adapted from an earlier version at CommonDreams.org and distributed for syndication by OtherWords.org.\", \"from\": 5029, \"to\": 5146, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This op-ed\", \"from\": 5029, \"to\": 5039}, {\"ngram\": \"an earlier version\", \"from\": 5057, \"to\": 5075}, {\"ngram\": \"syndication\", \"from\": 5116, \"to\": 5127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Views expressed in this article and may or may not reflect those ofConsortium News.\", \"from\": 5148, \"to\": 5231, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Views\", \"from\": 5148, \"to\": 5153}, {\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 5167, \"to\": 5179}, {\"ngram\": \"those ofConsortium News\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:2024 OlympicsCameroonPhyllis Bennis.Refugee CrisisU.S.\", \"from\": 5235, \"to\": 5294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tags:2024 OlympicsCameroonPhyllis Bennis\", \"from\": 5235, \"to\": 5275}, {\"ngram\": \"Refugee CrisisU.S.\", \"from\": 5276, \"to\": 5294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"sanctions The Refugee I do not belong to any one timeor to any one culture.I am with you always.\", \"from\": 5295, \"to\": 5393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5310, \"end\": 5317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.206405757119447e-19, \"text\": \"Refugee\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 5295, \"to\": 5304}, {\"ngram\": \"any one\", \"from\": 5336, \"to\": 5343}, {\"ngram\": \"timeor\", \"from\": 5344, \"to\": 5350}, {\"ngram\": \"any one culture\", \"from\": 5354, \"to\": 5369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For every inchgained in one place in one time,for my basic dignity,an inch or more is conceded inanother place and time.While it seems that this need not be so,it remains the truthof my life, my suffering, my fate.\", \"from\": 5394, \"to\": 5608, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every\", \"from\": 5398, \"to\": 5403}, {\"ngram\": \"one place\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5427}, {\"ngram\": \"one time\", \"from\": 5431, \"to\": 5439}, {\"ngram\": \"my basic dignity\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5460}, {\"ngram\": \"an inch\", \"from\": 5461, \"to\": 5468}, {\"ngram\": \"inanother place\", \"from\": 5489, \"to\": 5504}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 5509, \"to\": 5513}, {\"ngram\": \"the truthof\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5576}, {\"ngram\": \"my life\", \"from\": 5577, \"to\": 5584}, {\"ngram\": \"my suffering\", \"from\": 5586, \"to\": 5598}, {\"ngram\": \"my fate\", \"from\": 5600, \"to\": 5607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Atheist and idolatrous regimes,religious pretense, market forces,retribution and retaliation, all conspireto take the little bit I haveand steal or destroy it and my meager meansof survival, setting me on a path ofdespair.\", \"from\": 5610, \"to\": 5832, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all conspireto\", \"from\": 5704, \"to\": 5718}, {\"ngram\": \"the little bit\", \"from\": 5724, \"to\": 5738}, {\"ngram\": \"my meager meansof survival\", \"from\": 5773, \"to\": 5799}, {\"ngram\": \"a path ofdespair\", \"from\": 5815, \"to\": 5831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sometimes complicit withthese forces.\", \"from\": 5833, \"to\": 5875, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"complicit withthese forces\", \"from\": 5848, \"to\": 5874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I bought their lie thatviolence could improve my lot.\", \"from\": 5876, \"to\": 5929, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their lie thatviolence\", \"from\": 5885, \"to\": 5907}, {\"ngram\": \"my lot\", \"from\": 5922, \"to\": 5928}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thatrevolution would bring me peace.\", \"from\": 5930, \"to\": 5966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thatrevolution\", \"from\": 5930, \"to\": 5944}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 5960, \"to\": 5965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thatthe trade deal would bring prosperity.I am more oftenan unwitting victim.\", \"from\": 5967, \"to\": 6044, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thatthe trade deal\", \"from\": 5967, \"to\": 5985}, {\"ngram\": \"prosperity\", \"from\": 5998, \"to\": 6008}, {\"ngram\": \"more oftenan unwitting victim\", \"from\": 6014, \"to\": 6043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My age, my alreadytattered body, are given no consideration.If I am starved, maimed, or killed, itmatters not.In all likelihood, I will not be counted.At best, just some general statisticto be estimated, according to whicheverside of history is keeping tabs.I am hopeless and lost.\", \"from\": 6045, \"to\": 6326, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my alreadytattered body\", \"from\": 6053, \"to\": 6076}, {\"ngram\": \"no consideration\", \"from\": 6088, \"to\": 6104}, {\"ngram\": \"itmatters\", \"from\": 6141, \"to\": 6150}, {\"ngram\": \"all likelihood\", \"from\": 6158, \"to\": 6172}, {\"ngram\": \"just some general statisticto\", \"from\": 6205, \"to\": 6234}, {\"ngram\": \"whicheverside\", \"from\": 6262, \"to\": 6275}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 6279, \"to\": 6286}, {\"ngram\": \"tabs\", \"from\": 6298, \"to\": 6302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you do not want me wanderingacross your border, swimming toyour shore, then think carefully aboutwhat you do when you consign yourproxy to the greedy, the prideful,the moneyed interestswho can only conceive of more.Who affirm their absolute authority.Who are willing to exploit anyone andanything, anywhere, and at any cost.Their guns and bombs encircle me.Their drones persist to remind me thatI am at their mercy-though they have no mercy.They are not content to leave me inmy simple existence.\", \"from\": 6328, \"to\": 6827, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your border\", \"from\": 6366, \"to\": 6377}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming toyour shore\", \"from\": 6379, \"to\": 6400}, {\"ngram\": \"yourproxy\", \"from\": 6457, \"to\": 6466}, {\"ngram\": \"the moneyed interestswho\", \"from\": 6495, \"to\": 6519}, {\"ngram\": \"their absolute authority\", \"from\": 6557, \"to\": 6581}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 6609, \"to\": 6615}, {\"ngram\": \"any cost\", \"from\": 6646, \"to\": 6654}, {\"ngram\": \"Their guns\", \"from\": 6655, \"to\": 6665}, {\"ngram\": \"bombs\", \"from\": 6670, \"to\": 6675}, {\"ngram\": \"Their drones\", \"from\": 6688, \"to\": 6700}, {\"ngram\": \"thatI\", \"from\": 6722, \"to\": 6727}, {\"ngram\": \"their mercy\", \"from\": 6734, \"to\": 6745}, {\"ngram\": \"no mercy\", \"from\": 6763, \"to\": 6771}, {\"ngram\": \"inmy simple existence\", \"from\": 6805, \"to\": 6826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My poverty isno shield to those who must wieldtheir reckless control.\", \"from\": 6828, \"to\": 6897, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My poverty isno shield\", \"from\": 6828, \"to\": 6850}, {\"ngram\": \"reckless control\", \"from\": 6880, \"to\": 6896}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not want to be your tired and poor.I do not want to be anotherhuddled mass upon your teaming shore.I simply want to live my life here,devoid of the destruction brought on byillusory moral pretense of the narcissistic,megalomaniacs in their tit-for-tat games.Forgive mewhen my own actions have made mecomplicit in such evil.\", \"from\": 6899, \"to\": 7227, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mass\", \"from\": 6974, \"to\": 6978}, {\"ngram\": \"your teaming shore\", \"from\": 6984, \"to\": 7002}, {\"ngram\": \"my life\", \"from\": 7025, \"to\": 7032}, {\"ngram\": \"the destruction\", \"from\": 7048, \"to\": 7063}, {\"ngram\": \"byillusory moral pretense\", \"from\": 7075, \"to\": 7100}, {\"ngram\": \"tat\", \"from\": 7152, \"to\": 7155}, {\"ngram\": \"my own actions\", \"from\": 7177, \"to\": 7191}, {\"ngram\": \"mecomplicit\", \"from\": 7202, \"to\": 7213}, {\"ngram\": \"such evil\", \"from\": 7217, \"to\": 7226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"May I have the humility to love and forgiveas I leave the flaming rubble,the stolen plot of land,for a journey whose end is unsure.I cannot know now, whether I will findarms of welcome ormore rejection and death.It will likely be the latter.\", \"from\": 7229, \"to\": 7470, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the humility\", \"from\": 7240, \"to\": 7252}, {\"ngram\": \"the flaming rubble\", \"from\": 7283, \"to\": 7301}, {\"ngram\": \"the stolen plot\", \"from\": 7302, \"to\": 7317}, {\"ngram\": \"land\", \"from\": 7321, \"to\": 7325}, {\"ngram\": \"a journey\", \"from\": 7330, \"to\": 7339}, {\"ngram\": \"whose end\", \"from\": 7340, \"to\": 7349}, {\"ngram\": \"findarms\", \"from\": 7394, \"to\": 7402}, {\"ngram\": \"welcome ormore rejection\", \"from\": 7406, \"to\": 7430}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 7435, \"to\": 7440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Imust set out, fearful and with little hope,for it is the only choicegiven to me, your refugee.\", \"from\": 7471, \"to\": 7573, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Imust\", \"from\": 7478, \"to\": 7483}, {\"ngram\": \"little hope\", \"from\": 7510, \"to\": 7521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From \\\"Looking Out onto Our World: Explorations of Power, Dogma and a World Deserving Contemplation\\\" by TP Graf The world's chief belligerent hegemon, The United States and, more broadly, the West is responsible for burdening masses of people, who's countries do not sufficiently prostrate themselves to corporate interests.\", \"from\": 7575, \"to\": 7899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7678, \"end\": 7680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tipi\", \"score\": 0.9999893374374572, \"rank\": 1.0662507655271751e-05, \"text\": \"TP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tipi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tipi\"}, {\"begin\": 7681, \"end\": 7685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Count\", \"score\": 0.9996250665974703, \"rank\": 0.00037507402987888163, \"text\": \"Graf\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Count\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Count\"}, {\"begin\": 7730, \"end\": 7743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9964364624047096, \"rank\": 0.0035762818